# 2007-03-16.jmb.1: Accepting OpenOffice.org as Associated Project

### Whereas;

1. OpenOffice.org is a substantial and significant Free Software project.

2. The OpenOffice.org developers would like SPI's support and assistance,
including taking donations in the United States.

### The SPI Board Resolves That;

1. OpenOffice.org is formally invited to become an SPI Associated Project,
according to the SPI Framework for Associated Projects, SPI Resolution
1998-11-16.iwj.1-amended-2004-08-10.iwj.1, a copy of which can be found
at 
[http://www.spi-inc.org/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1](/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1)

2. The OpenOffice.org liaison to SPI will be elected by the OpenOffice.org
community council according to the process documented at
http://council.openoffice.org/advisor-process.html.  The initial liaison
will be Louis Suarez-Potts.

3. This invitation will lapse, if not accepted, 60 days after it is
approved by the SPI Board.

